      left]\ar [uurr, "" {name=G, above}, "G"', bend right]
      \ar [Rightarrow, from=1-2, to=3-2, "\eta "', shorten >= 1em, shorten <= 1em,
      xshift=-.2em, yshift=.4em]
      \ar [Rightarrow, dashed, from=Lan, to=G, "\exists !"', shorten <= .5em]
    \end {tikzcd}

Dually, the universal property of a right Kan extension asks for a natural
  bijection E^C(GK, F)\cong  \lbrack  E^D(G, \operatorname *{Ran}_K   F). Explicitly, this consists of a functor D\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{Ran}_K} F
  together with a natural transformation (\operatorname *{Ran}_K F) K\xrightarrow {\epsilon } F, as
  in




